<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="234" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[793,1399,1225,1409]" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,903,1225,1249]" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: The new species differs from the two previously known species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1325,1258,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Paraprosopis">
<emphasis box="[1191,1325,1258,1281]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">Paraprosopis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this region, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1924" box="[880,1080,1289,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnus">
<emphasis box="[880,1080,1289,1313]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">Hylaeus concinnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1310,1289,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrocallosus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1310,1289,1313]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="234">H. nigrocallosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the coarser and sparser punctation of the metasoma and the shagreen tergum 1. The part of the frons near the scape is without a smooth area. The male is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
